What Happened In 2019 😯

Tags: announcement

We are in the middle of gatherings, celebrations and reflections.

Several things happened during the year and we want to share them with you:

  • We accomplished our first year as a company!

  • We changed home to Our Community House.

  • We run several technical workshops and leadership intensives.

  • We defined Braneshop as a Living Business.

  • Our Community House, and University of Melbourne have interviewed us.

  • Esmeralda joined Braneshop!

  • We shared panels with Sheda, Code like a Girl between others.

  • We attended dozens of meetups, conferences and panels.

  • We organised events to learn about XAI and Ethics on AI.

  • Our showreel grew to more than 30 cool AI examples.

  • We gave 11 scholarships to attend our workshops!

  • We were on RRR’s show Byte In Into IT on the radio!

What’s next?

Melbourne’s first Datathon for Social Good!

Use your creativity, communication and collaboration to solve an interesting data-related problem. They’re opportunities to try new things, learn from others, build connections — and have fun! Register today!

Melbourne Knowledge Week

We’re teaming up with a friend to bring you a probably strange and hopefully thought-provoking installation at MKW Hub!

Workshops in February

Start the next year with energy!

  • On the 6th of February, we will quick off our next Technical Workshop edition.
  • On the 16th of March, we will have an intensive day of AI for Leadership.

One thing we’re truly grateful for is the support from our community, partners and supporters. Thank you for being on this rewarding journey with us.

We sincerely hope you had an incredible year.
